list.item:
—a possible alternative based on ex-President Paz Estensorro and the National Revolutionary Movement (MNR)
                        does not seem likely due to internal dissension within the MNR and strong
                        military opposition to a resumption of power by the MNR;

—neither does an alternative based on more moderate elements in the Army
                        seem probable. Indeed, Torres seems to have successfully forestalled such a
                        move in January;
